[{"id":"VR022178","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following best helps to explain why <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a, solid\"><math alttext=\"N a, solid\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Na</mtext><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is more reactive with water than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M g, solid\"><math alttext=\"M g, solid\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Mg</mtext><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR022178_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a, solid\"><math alttext=\"N a, solid\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Na</mtext><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is softer than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M g, solid\"><math alttext=\"M g, solid\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Mg</mtext><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The atomic mass of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a\"><math alttext=\"N a\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Na</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is less than that of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M g\"><math alttext=\"M g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Mg</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N a with a positive 1 charge \"><math alttext=\"N a with a positive 1 charge \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext>Na</mtext></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math>